               <head>Miscellaneous Sufi works of Ni‘matullah Vali and others (Persian, Arabic, and Hindavi), 22 works (a-x)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous works on Sufism, mainly by the poet and Ṣūfī leader, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657166.0x000001 viaf_33415216" role="aut">Nūr al-Dīn Niʿmat Allāh ibn ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Kirmānī</persName>, commonly known as <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657166.0x000001 viaf_33415216" role="aut">Niʿmat Allāh “Valī”</persName> (d. 834/1431). The first work (item a) is the earliest dated portion, Z̲ū al-Qaʿdah 1002/July-August 1594. Folios rebound, several damaged by wormholes; net overlay over some fragile folios. Bound in IOL red leather binding, preserving volume’s tooled leather covers (these are not original). Some seal impressions of later owners dated 1054/1644-5 and 1172/1759. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109389" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1148-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="4v">ff. 1v-4v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on Qādirī interpretations of perception through the five senses by an unnamed author writing around 1000/1591-2 at the request of one <persName key="person_f7601" role="pat">Shaykh Ṣadr Jahān</persName>, presumably identifiable with <persName key="person_f7511" role="pat">Ṣadr Jahān ibn Abū al-Fatḥ Pihānī</persName> (d. 1019/1610). 
Dated colophon (f. 4v): completed by <persName key="person_f7530" role="scr">Sayyid Ilyās</persName>, on the morning of Sunday Z̲ū al-Qaʿdah 10[02]/July-August 1594. Figures for the year are damaged by an intruding wormhole.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is written obliquely in miniscule nastaʿlīq, occasionally tending toward shikastah āmīz. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotation in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>This work is followed by a brief address to the novice Ṣūfī (f. 5r). Not dated. The hand matches the work of <persName key="person_f7530" role="scr">Sayyid Ilyās</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>This work is followed by a separate, but brief, untitled treatise on mystical love beginning with an Arabic introduction, including schematic diagrams (f. 6). Not dated. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21644">Ḥavāss-i khamsah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21644">حواسّ خمسه</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1148-item2">
                     <locus from="7v" to="8v">ff. 7v-8v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Unidentified treatise on spiritual matters by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Clear nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1148-item3">
                     <locus from="9v" to="10v">ff. 9v-10v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Brief collection of Ṣūfī exhortations by the poet and Ṣūfī leader, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657166.0x000001 viaf_33415216" role="aut">Nūr al-Dīn Niʿmat Allāh ibn ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Kirmānī</persName>, commonly known as <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657166.0x000001 viaf_33415216" role="aut">Niʿmat Allāh "Valī"</persName> (d. 834/1431). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Several notes at end indicating the work had been collated. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657166.0x000001 viaf_33415216" type="supplied">Niʿmat Allāh Valī, 1330?-1431</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_33415216" type="supplied">سيد نور الدين شاه نعمت الله ولى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21645">Sulūk-i naṣāʾiḥ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21645">سلوك نصائح</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91005357" n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1148-item4">
                     <locus from="11v" to="13v">ff. 11v-13v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of Ṣūfī aphorisms, each introduced as amānah, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
