                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85125350" n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1148-item5">
                     <locus from="14v" to="15r">ff. 14v-15r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on the nature of the soul, composed in alternating verses and summary prose passages, by the poet and Ṣūfī leader, <persName key="viaf_33415216" role="aut">Nūr al-Dīn Niʿmat Allāh ibn ʿAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Kirmānī</persName>, commonly known as <persName key="viaf_33415216" role="aut">Niʿmat Allāh "Valī"</persName> (d. 834/1431). 
